# Project rules (Cursor)

The source of truth for this project's AI instructions lives in `AGENTS.md`
and the `.ai/` folder. This file is a thin pointer — keep edits there, not
here.

## Always read

@AGENTS.md
@.ai/project.md
@.ai/rules.md

## Read when relevant

- `@.ai/architecture.md` — structural changes
- `@.ai/style.md` — naming / formatting / comments
- `@.ai/glossary.md` — unfamiliar domain terms
- `@.ai/skills/add-feature.md` — adding features
- `@.ai/skills/fix-bug.md` — bug fixes
- `@.ai/skills/refactor.md` — refactors
- `@.ai/skills/write-tests.md` — writing tests
- `@.ai/decisions/` — past architectural choices

## Behavior

- Follow the "Never" list in `.ai/rules.md` without exception.
- Match local patterns. Open sibling files before editing.
- Smallest correct change. No speculative abstractions or scope creep.
- Run the commands in `.ai/project.md` (lint, typecheck, tests) before
  declaring work done.
